AUDIO: 'This video covers how to use the expand tool. [music] The expand tool helps you improve lowfidelity areas in your generated world. Once you\'re inside [music] the generated world, click the create button in the bottom toolbar. To start expanding, click expand in the right sidebar. You\'ll see a warning if'

[00:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your target area is too close to the existing [music] scene or too far outside of it. Adjust your position. Then click expand here where you want the scene to grow. You can expand [music] one area per generation, but you can cue multiple'

[00:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'expansions while others are processing. Active expansions [music] appear in the right sidebar and can be selected once they finish. Expand works best [music] for improving areas like rooms, hallways, or parts of'

[00:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the scene just outside the main view. Expanded [music] results are generated randomly, but always match the style of the original environment.'
